<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1263671" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=500%2C389&#038;ssl=1" alt="BCDA executes 38 projects in Katsina, inaugurates health centre" width="500" height="389" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=1024%2C797&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=300%2C233&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=768%2C597&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=58%2C45&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=249%2C194&amp;ssl=1 249w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=167%2C130&amp;ssl=1 167w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?resize=560%2C436&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Katsina.jpg?w=1234&amp;ssl=1 1234w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Border Community Development Agency (BCDA) has executed more than 38 projects in Katsina state, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. The Executive Secretary of the agency, Alhaji Junaidu Abdullahi, made this known on Saturday in Maikoni village in Maiadua Local Government area while handing over a 24-bed capacity health centre to the state government. Abdullahi, who was represented by Alhaji Farouk Maiturare, Director, Project Development and Implementation of the agency, said that the health facility was part of the 38 intervention projects executed by the agency in the state. Abdullahi said that other projects executed at the border communities included water supply, classrooms, skills acquisition, empowerment programmes, and agricultural initiatives. According to him, the clinic comprised antenatal, family planning, immunization as well as male and female wards. Abdullahi urged the benefiting communities to make judicious use of the facilities, adding that the government would continue to consider border communities for more projects in order to give them a sense of belonging. In his remarks, Gov. Aminu Masari commended the agency for the numerous projects so far executed in the state, assuring that his administration would continue to cooperate with it to attract additional projects. Masari urged the community to make proper use of the facility and ensure good maintenance. He said that the state government would complement the efforts by supplying drugs and qualified health personnel to man the clinic. The governor used the occasion to advise border communities on the need to be security conscious, urging them to report any strange face or movement to appropriate authorities for prompt action. vanguard The Border Community Development Agency(BCDA) has intervened in the construction of some critical projects for the benefits of border communities in Jigawa. April 26, 2019 In "News" The Border Communities Development Agency, BCDA says its plans to provide basic social amenities for neglected Nigerian border communities will tackle most of  the security threat the country faces. September 19, 2019 In "News" By Henry Umoru - Abuja The Senate Wednesday came hard on the Management team of the Border Communities Development Agency ( BCDA), following the refusal of the latter to state locations for the N3.626billion capital projects the agency proposed for the 2020 fiscal year. Subsequently, the senate gave the BCDA,… October 23, 2019 In "News"